column1:
I'm with you there. This time was a little too
close.
But why did Akane-chan become a Monarch?

It sounded like Akane-chan kinda had her own
agenda... Is that what makes you a Monarch,
though?

Well, one thing's for certain, Akane was made
into a Monarch to capture us.
If I had to guess, Konoe's the one who set this up.

Although I'm not sure if he was acting on
Owada's orders or just on his own...

Do you think Konoe made Alice and Natsume
into Monarchs too?

Yeah, I wouldn't be surprised... But it probably
wasn't for the same reason he made Akane into
one. That part remains a mystery.

Playing with other people's hearts like that... He
won't get away with this.
Yeah. Just you wait, you goat-chinned mother—

Is it gone...? Looks like they haven't found this
place just yet.
We're stuck here unless we do something...

[1B]S1, incoming phone call from a
"Sae Niijima."

It's been some time. Do you remember me?
It's Sae Niijima.
As if I'd ever forget you?
You've been well, I take it?
Glad to see I was of some help.
Yes, as well as I can be at the moment.

*sigh* Sounds like you've stuck your nose
into something big again.

Is everyone else with you? Could you put me on
speaker?
It's good to hear you're all okay.

Sis... Thank you. I knew you'd come through for
us.

You owe me big for this one. My help doesn't
come cheap, you know?

For real, you really saved our asses. We woulda
been totally boned if you hadn't got Gramps out.

Gorgeous and professional! That's a recipe for a
femme fatale super lawyer, if I've ever seen one.

Flattery won't get you anywhere, just so you're
aware. Plus, I can't take all the credit.
Anyway, I have some good news.

The arrest warrant for the Phantom Thieves has
been voided. That should keep the police off
your backs for the time being.

The arrest warrant didn't have a judge's seal.
What's more, the evidence submitted was fake.

It seems like someone wanted you all arrested,
and they didn't care what for, so long as it was
done.

Not only that, but it turns out the Public Security
Bureau had a hand in Inspector Hasegawa's
unlawful investigation.

The prefectural police are scrambling to cover
this up right now. They can't afford to be out
looking for you.

I'll contact you if anything happens. In the
meantime, just focus on getting out of your
current predicament, okay?
You can thank me once this case is closed.

Just make it back in one piece. No better way to
say thanks.

That's my line. Look after Makoto for me, won't
you?

All right, I have business to take care of. I'm
looking forward to hearing from you again.

How encouraging. To know there are others out
there who support us...
Mmhm, we'll need to do all we can to succeed, for their sakes too.

Now we just gotta come up with a plan... What
should we do?

If Konoe is responsible for changing everyone's
hearts, then it's likely this case will be resolved
once we change his heart.
Yeah, and we'll clear our names, too!
Right. We won't be suspects in the director's murder anymore either.
But... we still don't have the keyword for Konoe's Jail.
He seems to be more aware of our activities than we expected. I doubt we'll be able to carry out Zenkichi's plan at this point.

And that's not all. If he knows about us, then he
probably knows to keep his keyword safe as well.

It's safe to assume he won't just carelessly let it
slip out, not while his heart's liable to be
changed...
Up shit creek without a paddle... Now what?

We just need someone who can get Konoe's 
keyword without raising suspicion, is that right?
Do you know of such a person?

Of course. Ichinose-san's the one who
developed EMMA, and she's had contact with
Konoe, thanks to the lecture at the university...

Ichinose-san might be able to get Konoe's
keyword without seeming out of place.
This just might work. Good job, Sophia!
A piece of cake, as they say.

See if you can call her up right now,
[1B]S1!

Ah, hello there, [1B]S1-kun! You
seem to be doing okay. That's great to hear.
Truly brightens my day!
We're in a bit of a pinch.

Not every day I get a call from you. And I'm sure
you have something interesting for me, so I can't
help but be excited!

So, did something happen? Or, wait, lemme back
up a bit. How did things go in Okinawa?

Hm? Did something happen? Or, wait, lemme
back up a bit. How did things go in Okinawa?

Oh, right... We never told Ichinose-san
about Okinawa.

That's true. We should fill her in on what's been
going on.

Ah, it sounds like you're all together. Okay, let's
hear it!

I see, I see... It seems you're caught up in
another crazy adventure, as usual!
Hey, this ain't nothin' to laugh about.
Oops, I guess that wasn't right of me...
I think I understand what's going on.
So you're after Konoe-san's keyword, right?
Right, do you think you can get it out of him?
Well, asking him for it might be kind of weird...
I mean, I already got it from him a while ago.

Well, the day you guys came to that lecture,
there was a little social gathering afterward for
some of the bigger names involved...

It was there I ran into Konoe-san and he gave me
his business card. The keyword was right there
on the front.

Huh? Now, where'd I put it? I'm pretty sure I had
it right here...
P-Please, you gotta find it! This is top-priority!
I think it was around here somewhere...

I-I'll make sure I find it by tomorrow! Have a
nice day!!!

And it's gonna take till tomorrow? How messy
do you think her room is?

A small price to pay, but if this gets us his
keyword...
Mmhm, we'll be able to enter Konoe's Jail!
Can we really count on her, though?

I'm not so sure, but we don't have any other
options right now.

Yeah. Let's just make sure we're prepared for
when we finally infiltrate the Jail.

Tomorrow, we'll link up with Zenkichi and head
to Osaka!
